  "texts": [
    "[Heb98, Lau10, JP17, BL18, BL23a].",
    "Many of these applications rely on a Kirwan-Ness stratification of the variety of Lie algebras.",
    "One associates to each metric Lie algebra (𝔫, h) a uniquely-determined h-self-adjoint endomorphism β h ∈ End(𝔫), called the GIT weights.",
    "Its conjugacy class is independent of h and serves as a label for the stratum containing the Lie algebra 𝔫.We now list some properties of the GIT weights that are key in some of the proofs in this article.",
    "We refer the reader to [BL21] and therein references for proofs and further details."
  ],
